criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        High-risk cardiac surgery patients as determined by at least one of the followings:

          -  the age greater than or equal to 75 years on the day of screening;

          -  left ventricle ejection fraction less than 35%;

          -  use of a preoperative intraaortic balloon pump;

          -  combined valve and coronary artery surgery or multiple valve surgery in patients who
             have congestive heart failure, or renal insufficiency (creatinine clearance < 60
             ml/min)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  refusal of consent
